description:
&lt;p&gt;The Tissue Viability team require a Clinical Nurse Specialist with a passion for wound care to support the small team in delivering complex wound care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be key in supporting the Lead Nurse with the development and management of the service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be involved in all aspects of complex wound assessment and management across the Trust working closely with the clinical teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have advanced knowledge and skills in various aspects of wound assessment and management underpinned by excellent communication skills. Candidates must possess an ability to work both autonomously and as part of a team, be flexible to change, have audit experience and computer skills. Experience of and willingness to implement and sustain change is also essential. The Clinical Nurse Specialist will be expected to produce and deliver ongoing training sessions, audit feedback and review materials and teaching style on a regular basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 16.5 Hours part time role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal discussion please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Siobhan Mccoulough&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead Tissue Viability Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Siobhan.mccoulough@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
